5:
By the way, thanks for taking
Firamelia in! She could use good
company like you!
9:
Uh... I think you're giving us too much
credit.
12:
Not at all! You know, she didn't use
to walk around aboveground until
you guys came along.
15:
Judging by your reaction though...
Has she not told you about her
situation?
19:
Nope, she hasn't said anything. I
figured she had a reason she
wanted to stay in Starview, but I
didn't pry.
23: She loves her secrets, that one...
27:
Oh, I can't wait for dinner. Alk's
cooking one of his amazing stews...
35:
...Did you need something from me,
priest?
38:
Our beloved guiding Star, you need
not look upon me with such
suspicion in your eyes!
40:
I don't recall consenting to
becoming such a thing. Now if you'll
excuse me.
43:
...Being stubborn is one thing, but
this is a little absurd, don't you think?
45:
My apologies, but this is all for your
own good.
46:
Please follow us to our
congregation. I swear you will be
treated well, as befitting your status.
48:
Yes, as our new leader... Granted to
us from the heavens, blessed with
the power of light and its guiding
ways!
51:
Are you quite done? I'm going to
have to report you to the Guild if you
keep this up.
52:
I assume you know the
consequences of being on the
Guild's bad side.
55:
Why do you insist on fraternizing
with those adventurer hooligans? It
is unbecoming of one wielding your
sacred power!
57:
If you won't come along of your own
free will, then I am afraid we shall
resort to force...
61:
They've grown far too bold lately.
Whatever am I to do with those
fools...
67:
Oh! Welcome back, Firamelia. I'll
heat up some food for you right now.
70: Stella, time to get up. She's back.
78: Did you stay up waiting for me?
82:
Hmm, kinda? There's something we
wanna apologize for...
86:
I see, so you heard everything from
Lilie.
92:
It's all right. I wasn't purposely trying
to hide any of it.
94:
But I'll have to give Lilie a stern
talking-to later.
98:
Never one to beat around the bush,
huh?
100:
Hehe, that's one perk of being an
adventurerhaving the freedom to
speak your mind.
103:
It's just too bad that some people
won't listen, no matter how clearly
you put it.
109:
So you've got a religious stalker
problem, huh?
113:
Not how I would refer to them, but
yes.
114:
They seem to mistakenly believe I
am some sort of holy figure.
119:
Have you heard of the Church of
Farlana? It's a faith that originated
from the Farlands, as you might
have guessed from the name.
120:
They worship the light of the stars,
you see. Apparently the religion first
came about when a sage guided a
group of travelers by starlight.
123:
Ah, those people that run around
saying, "May the Stars guide you."
126:
Exactly. They REALLY love their stars,
lights, and guides...
131:
And I happen to be all about light
magic and guiding.
134:
Yeah... It's no surprise they keep
hounding you.
137:
For quite some time too. I can't get
rid of them.
146:
I'll admit, it's flattering to be so
sought after. But I wish they'd
understand that I have my own road
to take.
149:
It's like... If you saved a village, and
the grateful villagers ask you to
settle down there. Would you?
151:
You'd be set for the rest of your life.
No worries, all your needs taken
care of.
153:
But that would be the end of your
journey. Could you do it?
161:
Me neither. I'd appreciate the offer,
but we've got things we need to see
through.
168:
I'm the same. There's a path ahead
of me I have to walk, and I have to
use my power to do it.
169:
I could never sit still and be
worshippedmy power coveted, but
never used. The priests and I will
never see eye to eye.
176:
Hehe... It's kind of you to be
concerned.
179:
But I walk this path proudly. To do
otherwise would be wasting my
potential.
181:
Just like how you should keep 
your heads held high 
and stay your course.
186:
Feels like we got comforted instead,
huh?
193:
A bit, but I guess I never needed to...
Man, she's got her stuff together.
